Let \( |\Psi_0\rangle := |\zeta_r\rangle_{i,j} \otimes |\psi\rangle_{k_1,\ldots,k_n} \), and \( \rho_0 := |\Psi_0\rangle \langle\Psi_0| \). Now, define

\[
|\Psi_L\rangle := (\hat{I}_i \otimes \hat{W}_{j,k_1}) |\Psi_0\rangle,
\]
\[
|\Psi_R\rangle := (\hat{W}_{i,k_1}^T \otimes \hat{I}_j) |\Psi_0\rangle, \tag{G1}
\]

and let \( \rho_L = |\Psi_L\rangle \langle\Psi_L| \), \( \rho_R = |\Psi_R\rangle \langle\Psi_R| \). Hence, the fidelity between \( \rho_L \) and \( \rho_R \) is

\[
= \left| \operatorname{tr}(\rho_0 \hat{V}) \right|^2. \tag{G2}
\]
